    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664493",
        "quote": "We have this interesting problem with black holes. What is a black hole? It is a region of space where you have mass that's confined to zero volume, which means that the density is infinitely large, which means we have no way of describing, really, what a black hole is!",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrea M. Ghez",
            "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664493"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Mass",
                "url": "/topics/mass"
            },
            {
                "name": "Infinitely",
                "url": "/topics/infinitely"
            },
            {
                "name": "Confined",
                "url": "/topics/confined"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664490",
        "quote": "The question that I started off with was, I thought, very simple. It was just 'Is there a massive black hole at the center of the Milky Way?' But one of the things I love about science is that you always end up with new questions.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrea M. Ghez",
            "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664490"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Love",
                "url": "/topics/love"
            },
            {
                "name": "Thought",
                "url": "/topics/thought"
            },
            {
                "name": "Very",
                "url": "/topics/very"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664492",
        "quote": "The atmosphere is great for people - it allows us to survive - but it's a real headache for astronomers.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrea M. Ghez",
            "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664492"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Survive",
                "url": "/topics/survive"
            },
            {
                "name": "Real",
                "url": "/topics/real"
            },
            {
                "name": "Atmosphere",
                "url": "/topics/atmosphere"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664480",
        "quote": "An ordinary black hole is thought to be the end state of a really massive star's life.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrea M. Ghez",
            "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664480"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Thought",
                "url": "/topics/thought"
            },
            {
                "name": "Hole",
                "url": "/topics/hole"
            },
            {
                "name": "Massive",
                "url": "/topics/massive"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664485",
        "quote": "There's a large cluster of stars that are orbiting the center of our galaxy. And by measuring the motion of stars, and in particular, their orbits, we can figure out whether or not there's a central black hole.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrea M. Ghez",
            "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664485"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Measuring",
                "url": "/topics/measuring"
            },
            {
                "name": "Cluster",
                "url": "/topics/cluster"
            },
            {
                "name": "Figure",
                "url": "/topics/figure"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664478",
        "quote": "I'm interested in finding whether or not there is a really massive, what we like to call 'super massive' black hole at the center of our galaxy. And the reason this is interesting is that it gives us an opportunity to prove whether or not these exotic objects really exist.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrea M. Ghez",
            "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664478"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Prove",
                "url": "/topics/prove"
            },
            {
                "name": "Reason",
                "url": "/topics/reason"
            },
            {
                "name": "Objects",
                "url": "/topics/objects"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664484",
        "quote": "Our galaxy's pretty ordinary, garden-variety. So if we believe our galaxy has a super massive black hole, that tells us that most, if not all, galaxies host such a black hole at their centers.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrea M. Ghez",
            "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664484"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Black",
                "url": "/topics/black"
            },
            {
                "name": "Pretty",
                "url": "/topics/pretty"
            },
            {
                "name": "Galaxies",
                "url": "/topics/galaxies"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_552746",
        "quote": "The key to proving that there's a black hole is showing that there's a tremendous amount of mass in a very small volume. And you can do that with the motions of stars.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrea M. Ghez",
            "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_552746"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Small",
