            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_552747",
        "quote": "The Keck telescope, which is the largest in the world, had opened just before I began my faculty position at UCLA.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrea M. Ghez",
            "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_552747"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Before",
                "url": "/topics/before"
            },
            {
                "name": "Which",
                "url": "/topics/which"
            },
            {
                "name": "Largest",
                "url": "/topics/largest"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_552749",
        "quote": "Fortunately, most things around the supermassive black hole are just going to go around it. They're going to orbit it. They don't actually get sucked in.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrea M. Ghez",
            "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_552749"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Black",
                "url": "/topics/black"
            },
            {
                "name": "Going",
                "url": "/topics/going"
            },
            {
                "name": "Go",
                "url": "/topics/go"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664477",
        "quote": "How do you observe something you can't see? This is the basic question of somebody who's interested in finding and studying black holes. Because black holes are objects whose pull of gravity is so intense that nothing can escape it, not even light, so you can't see it directly.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrea M. Ghez",
            "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664477"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Observe",
                "url": "/topics/observe"
            },
            {
                "name": "Objects",
                "url": "/topics/objects"
            },
            {
                "name": "How",
                "url": "/topics/how"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664481",
        "quote": "Black holes are very exotic objects. Technically, a black hole puts a huge amount of mass inside of zero volume. So our understanding of the center of black holes doesn't make sense, which is a big clue to physicists that we don't have our physics quite right.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrea M. Ghez",
            "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664481"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Big",
                "url": "/topics/big"
            },
            {
                "name": "Very",
                "url": "/topics/very"
            },
            {
                "name": "Objects",
                "url": "/topics/objects"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664482",
        "quote": "As an astronomer, I get to ignore the details of the things that we don't understand. There's a lot of work that we can do on scales that we do understand, and there is actually a finite size that I can associate with a super massive black hole.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrea M. Ghez",
            "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664482"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Work",
                "url": "/topics/work"
            },
            {
                "name": "Understand",
                "url": "/topics/understand"
            },
            {
                "name": "Finite",
                "url": "/topics/finite"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664483",
        "quote": "The key to proving that there's a black hole is showing that there's a tremendous amount of mass in a very small volume. And you can do that with the motions of stars. The way the star moves around the center of the galaxy is very much like the way the planets orbit the sun.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrea M. Ghez",
            "url": "/quotes/andrea_m_ghez_664483"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Small",
